				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Perhaps I was a little unclear with my last post.. though a couple people got it <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /> If there are too many people/npc's/etc on a mob's agro list. A charmed mob is INCAPABLE of holding agro. It's coded to not hold agro over a certain number(I still want to say 3 but its been a long time since I've played around with that). Theres no way to change it by level of pets / pc's / etc.  It just can't do it. It was coded in awhile back so people couldn't.. well.. charm rapist mobs and have a whole group of casters or whatnot nuking a mob down for super fast xp and for other reasons along those lines. 
<br />

<br />
Level of a pc's pets holding agro over one another is a different story. I'm only talking about when this involves a charmed pet <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Xeg-<a href="http://www.havenlight.com" target="_blank">Havenlight</a>
