			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Actually, you can have up to 5 spots on the hate list before the mob outright ignores charmed pet aggro.  I regularly group with a chanter and a druid in HoH, and the charmed pet does not lose aggro.  The hate list consists of:
<br />

<br />
1. Me
<br />
2. My pet
<br />
3. Chanter
<br />
4. Chanter's Charmed Pet
<br />
5. Druid (Snare/Heal)
<br />

<br />
It is when you go over 5 that you get in trouble.  To also back up what someone else was saying, the pet that gets aggro is the pet that is closest to the mob.  I find that RS tends to stay far enough back that it rarely gets aggro, and simply backing off and reengaging will normally fix it.  Since Mage pets tend to stay farther back than most pets, they are pretty safe with this plan.
<br />

<br />
Ledorus
<br />
Elven Archmage of Quellious<br />_________________<br />Ledorus Nolitari
<br />
Elven Archmage of Quellious
<br />
