			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This entire question's answer lies in the charmed pet nerf from a while back.  They completely changed the way charmed pets can hold aggro.  When there's so many people on the hate list of the mob being attacked, it is almost impossible for the charmed pet to hold aggro over anything else, including other pets.  
<br />

<br />
I used to do the BoT minis (Laef, Oreen, Guakr, Hreindar) way back with just an enchanter and a druid.  The enchanter would charm, I would use my summoned pet, and the druid would just heal.  After the charm nerf, my pet <span style="font-style: italic">always</span> tanked the giants.  It never failed--if I send my pet after a mob that a charmed pet is tanking, my pet tanks.  That's been the case for several, several months as well.  I've run into this same problem in Tipt, where a tanking charmed pet cannot hold aggro over my pet.<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro
<br />
<a href="http://www.furiouspantaloons.org"><i>Furious Pantaloons</i></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
